[905.622501, "o", "\u001b[7;1HThis behavior depends on the policy and functionality of the unde\u001b[7;66H\\\u001b[8;1Hrlying\u001b[K\u001b[9;1H‘chmod’ system call.  When in doubt, check the underlying system\u001b[10;1Hbehavior.\u001b[K\u001b[11;1H\u001b[K\u001b[12;1H   If used, MODE specifies the new file mode bits.  For details, \u001b[12;66H\\\u001b[13;1Hsee the\u001b[K\u001b[14;1Hsection on \u001b[4m*note File permissions\u001b[24m::.  If you really want MODE to \u001b[K\u001b[14;66H\\\u001b[15;1H\u001b[K\u001b[15;1Hhave a\u001b[16;1Hleading ‘-’, you should use ‘--’ first, e.g., ‘chmod -- -w file’.\u001b[16;1H\u001b[1;66H\\\u001b[5;66H\\\u001b[7;66H\\\u001b[12;66H\\\u001b[14;66H\\\u001b[16;1H"]
[905.653581, "o", "\u001b[16;1H\u001b[17;1H\u001b[7m-----Info: (coreutils)chmod invocation, 120 lines --30%-----------\u001b[0m\u001b[1;1Hroup ID\u001b[K\u001b[2;1Hor one of the user’s supplementary group IDs, unless the user has\u001b[3;1Happropriate privileges.  Additional restrictions may cause the\u001b[K"]
[905.653769, "o", "\u001b[4;1Hset-user-ID and set-group-ID bits of MODE or REF_FILE to be ignor\u001b[4;66H\\\u001b[5;1Hed.\u001b[K\u001b[6;1HThis behavior depends on the policy and functionality of the unde\u001b[6;66H\\\u001b[7;1Hrlying\u001b[K\u001b[8;1H‘chmod’ system call.  When in doubt, check the underlying system\u001b[9;1Hbehavior.\u001b[K\u001b[10;1H\u001b[K\u001b[11;1H   If used, MODE specifies the new file mode bits.  For details, "]
[905.653851, "o", "\u001b[11;66H\\\u001b[12;1Hsee the\u001b[K\u001b[13;1Hsection on \u001b[4m*note File permissions\u001b[24m::.  If you really want MODE to \u001b[K\u001b[13;66H\\\u001b[14;1H\u001b[K\u001b[14;1Hhave a\u001b[15;1Hleading ‘-’, you should use ‘--’ first, e.g., ‘chmod -- -w file’.\u001b[16;1HTypically, though, ‘chmod a-w file’ is preferable, and ‘chmod -w \u001b[16;66H\\\u001b[16;1H\u001b[4;66H\\\u001b[6;66H\\\u001b[11;66H\\\u001b[13;66H\\\u001b[16;66H\\\u001b[16;1H"]
[905.685168, "o", "\u001b[16;1H\u001b[17;1H\u001b[7m-----Info: (coreutils)chmod invocation, 120 lines --31%-----------\u001b[0m\u001b[1;1Hor one of the user’s supplementary group IDs, unless the user has\u001b[2;1Happropriate privileges.  Additional restrictions may cause the\u001b[K\u001b[3;1Hset-user-ID and set-group-ID bits of MODE or REF_FILE to be ignor\u001b[3;66H\\\u001b[4;1Hed.\u001b[K\u001b[5;1HThis behavior depends on the policy and functionality of the unde\u001b[5;66H\\\u001b[6;1Hrlying\u001b[K\u001b[7;1H‘chmod’ system call.  When in doubt, check the underlying system\u001b[8;1Hbehavior.\u001b[K\u001b[9;1H\u001b[K"]
[905.685365, "o", "\u001b[10;1H   If used, MODE specifies the new file mode bits.  For details, \u001b[10;66H\\\u001b[11;1Hsee the\u001b[K\u001b[12;1Hsection on \u001b[4m*note File permissions\u001b[24m::.  If you really want MODE to \u001b[K\u001b[12;66H\\\u001b[13;1H\u001b[K\u001b[13;1Hhave a\u001b[14;1Hleading ‘-’, you should use ‘--’ first, e.g., ‘chmod -- -w file’.\u001b[15;1HTypically, though, ‘chmod a-w file’ is preferable, and ‘chmod -w \u001b[15;66H\\\u001b[16;1Hfile’\u001b[K\u001b[16;1H\u001b[3;66H\\\u001b[5;66H\\\u001b[10;66H\\\u001b[12;66H\\\u001b[15;66H\\\u001b[16;1H"]
[907.209334, "o", "\u001b[16;1H\u001b[17;1H\u001b[7m-----Info: (coreutils)chmod invocation, 120 lines --32%-----------\u001b[0m\u001b[1;1Happropriate privileges.  Additional restrictions may cause the\u001b[K\u001b[2;1Hset-user-ID and set-group-ID bits of MODE or REF_FILE to be ignor\u001b[2;66H\\\u001b[3;1Hed.\u001b[K\u001b[4;1HThis behavior depends on the policy and functionality of the unde\u001b[4;66H\\\u001b[5;1Hrlying\u001b[K\u001b[6;1H‘chmod’ system call.  When in doubt, check the underlying system\u001b[7;1Hbehavior.\u001b[K\u001b[8;1H\u001b[K\u001b[9;1H   If used, MODE specifies the new file mode bits.  For details, \u001b[9;66H\\\u001b[10;1Hsee the\u001b[K\u001b[11;1Hsection on \u001b[4m*note File permissions\u001b[24m::.  If you really want MODE to \u001b[K\u001b[11;66H\\\u001b[12;1H\u001b[K\u001b[12;1Hhave a\u001b[13;1Hleading ‘-’, you should use ‘--’ first, e.g., ‘chmod -- -w file’.\u001b[14;1HTypically, though, ‘chmod a-w file’ is preferable, and ‘chmod -w \u001b[14;66H\\\u001b[15;1Hfile’\u001b[K\u001b[16;1H(without the ‘--’) complains if it behaves differently from what \u001b[16;66H\\\u001b[16;1H\u001b[2;66H\\\u001b[4;66H\\\u001b[9;66H\\\u001b[11;66H\\\u001b[14;66H\\\u001b[16;66H\\\u001b[16;1H"]
