[907.960603, "o", "\u001b[2;1Hsection on \u001b[4m*note File permissions\u001b[24m::.  If you really want MODE to \u001b[K\u001b[2;66H\\\u001b[3;1H\u001b[K\u001b[3;1Hhave a\u001b[4;1Hleading ‘-’, you should use ‘--’ first, e.g., ‘chmod -- -w file’.\u001b[5;1HTypically, though, ‘chmod a-w file’ is preferable, and ‘chmod -w \u001b[5;66H\\\u001b[6;1Hfile’\u001b[K\u001b[7;1H(without the ‘--’) complains if it behaves differently from what \u001b[7;66H\\\u001b[8;1H‘chmod\u001b[K\u001b[9;1Ha-w file’ would do.\u001b[10;1H\u001b[K\u001b[11;1H   The program accepts the following options.  Also see \u001b[4m*note Com\u001b[24m\u001b[K\u001b[11;66H\\\u001b[12;1H\u001b[4mmon\u001b[24m\u001b[K\u001b[13;1H\u001b[4moptions\u001b[24m::.\u001b[K\u001b[14;1H\u001b[K\u001b[15;1H‘-c’\u001b[16;3H-changes’\u001b[16;1H\u001b[2;66H\\\u001b[5;66H\\\u001b[7;66H\\\u001b[11;66H\\\u001b[16;1H"]
