[908.023241, "o", "\u001b[16;1H\u001b[17;1H\u001b[7m-----Info: (coreutils)chmod invocation, 120 lines --43%-----------\u001b[0m\u001b[1;1H\u001b[K\u001b[1;1Hhave a\u001b[2;1Hleading ‘-’, you should use ‘--’ first, e.g., ‘chmod -- -w file’.\u001b[3;1HTypically, though, ‘chmod a-w file’ is preferable, and ‘chmod -w \u001b[3;66H\\\u001b[4;1Hfile’\u001b[K\u001b[5;1H(without the ‘--’) complains if it behaves differently from what \u001b[5;66H\\\u001b[6;1H‘chmod\u001b[K\u001b[7;1Ha-w file’ would do.\u001b[8;1H\u001b[K\u001b[9;1H   The program accepts the following options.  Also see \u001b[4m*note Com\u001b[24m\u001b[K\u001b[9;66H\\\u001b[10;1H\u001b[4mmon\u001b[24m\u001b[K\u001b[11;1H\u001b[4moptions\u001b[24m::.\u001b[K\u001b[12;1H\u001b[K\u001b[13;1H‘-c’\u001b[14;3H-changes’\u001b[15;1H     Verbosely describe the action for each FILE whose permission\u001b[15;66H\\\u001b[16;1Hs\u001b[K\u001b[16;1H\u001b[3;66H\\\u001b[5;66H\\\u001b[9;66H\\\u001b[15;66H\\\u001b[16;1H"]
