[917.177164, "o", "\u001b[16;1H\u001b[1;1H\u001b[K\u001b[2;1H   Any FILE argument that does not exist is created empty, unless\u001b[2;66H\\\u001b[3;2Hoption\u001b[K\u001b[4;1H‘--no-create’ (‘-c’) or ‘--no-dereference’ (‘-h’) was in effect.\u001b[5;1H\u001b[K\u001b[6;1H   A FILE argument string of ‘-’ is handled specially and causes \u001b[6;66H\\\u001b[7;1H‘touch’\u001b[K\u001b[8;1Hto change the times of the file associated with standard output.\u001b[9;1H\u001b[K\u001b[10;1H   By default, ‘touch’ sets file timestamps to the current time.\u001b[11;1HBecause ‘touch’ acts on its operands left to right, the resulting\u001b[12;1Htimestamps of earlier and later operands may disagree.\u001b[K\u001b[13;1H\u001b[K\u001b[14;1H   When setting file timestamps to the current time, ‘touch’ can \u001b[14;66H\\\u001b[15;1Hchange\u001b[K\u001b[16;1Hthe timestamps for files that the user does not own but has write\u001b[16;1H\u001b[2;66H\\\u001b[6;66H\\\u001b[14;66H\\\u001b[16;1H"]
