[920.661311, "o", "\u001b[16;1H\u001b[1;3H-no-dereference’\u001b[2;1H     Attempt to change the timestamps of a symbolic link, rather \u001b[2;66H\\\u001b[3;1Hthan\u001b[K\u001b[4;1H     what the link refers to.  When using this option, empty file\u001b[4;66H\\\u001b[5;1Hs are\u001b[K\u001b[6;1H     not created, but option ‘-c’ must also be used to avoid warn\u001b[6;66H\\\u001b[7;1Hing\u001b[K\u001b[8;1H     about files that do not exist.  Not all systems support chan\u001b[8;66H\\\u001b[9;1Hging\u001b[K\u001b[10;1H     the timestamps of symlinks, since underlying system support \u001b[10;66H\\\u001b[11;1Hfor\u001b[K\u001b[12;1H     this action was not required until POSIX 2008.  Also, on som\u001b[12;66H\\\u001b[13;1He\u001b[K\u001b[14;1H     systems, the mere act of examining a symbolic link changes t\u001b[14;66H\\\u001b[15;1Hhe\u001b[K\u001b[16;1H     access timestamp, such that only changes to the modification\u001b[16;1H\u001b[2;66H\\\u001b[4;66H\\\u001b[6;66H\\\u001b[8;66H\\\u001b[10;66H\\\u001b[12;66H\\\u001b[14;66H\\\u001b[16;1H"]
