[921.100262, "o", "\u001b[16;1H\u001b[1;1Hhe\u001b[K\u001b[2;1H     access timestamp, such that only changes to the modification\u001b[3;6Htimestamp will persist long enough to be observable.  When c\u001b[3;66H\\\u001b[4;1Houpled\u001b[K\u001b[5;1H     with option ‘-r’, a reference timestamp is taken from a symb\u001b[5;66H\\\u001b[6;1Holic\u001b[K\u001b[7;1H     link rather than the file it refers to.\u001b[8;1H\u001b[K\u001b[9;1H‘-m’\u001b[10;3H-time=mtime’\u001b[11;10Hodify’\u001b[12;1H     Change the modification timestamp only.\u001b[13;1H\u001b[K\u001b[14;1H‘-r FILE’\u001b[15;3H-reference=FILE’\u001b[16;1H     Use the times of the reference FILE instead of the current t\u001b[16;66H\\\u001b[16;1H\u001b[3;66H\\\u001b[5;66H\\\u001b[16;66H\\\u001b[16;1H"]
[921.131444, "o", "\u001b[16;1H\u001b[17;1H\u001b[7m-----Info: (coreutils)touch invocation, 173 lines --64%-----------\u001b[0m\u001b[1;1H     access timestamp, such that only changes to the modification\u001b[2;6Htimestamp will persist long enough to be observable.  When c\u001b[2;66H\\\u001b[3;1Houpled\u001b[K\u001b[4;1H     with option ‘-r’, a reference timestamp is taken from a symb\u001b[4;66H\\\u001b[5;1Holic\u001b[K\u001b[6;1H     link rather than the file it refers to.\u001b[7;1H\u001b[K\u001b[8;1H‘-m’\u001b[9;3H-time=mtime’\u001b[10;10Hodify’\u001b[11;1H     Change the modification timestamp only.\u001b[12;1H\u001b[K\u001b[13;1H‘-r FILE’\u001b[14;3H-reference=FILE’\u001b[15;1H     Use the times of the reference FILE instead of the current t\u001b[15;66H\\\u001b[16;1Hime.\u001b[K\u001b[16;1H\u001b[2;66H\\\u001b[4;66H\\\u001b[15;66H\\\u001b[16;1H"]
[921.16312, "o", "\u001b[16;1H\u001b[1;6Htimestamp will persist long enough to be observable.  When c\u001b[1;66H\\\u001b[2;1Houpled\u001b[K\u001b[3;1H     with option ‘-r’, a reference timestamp is taken from a symb\u001b[3;66H\\\u001b[4;1Holic\u001b[K\u001b[5;1H     link rather than the file it refers to.\u001b[6;1H\u001b[K\u001b[7;1H‘-m’\u001b[8;3H-time=mtime’\u001b[9;10Hodify’\u001b[10;1H     Change the modification timestamp only.\u001b[11;1H\u001b[K\u001b[12;1H‘-r FILE’\u001b[13;3H-reference=FILE’\u001b[14;1H     Use the times of the reference FILE instead of the current t\u001b[14;66H\\\u001b[15;1Hime.\u001b[K\u001b[16;1H     If this option is combined with the ‘--date=TIME’ (‘-d TIME’\u001b[16;66H\\\u001b[16;1H\u001b[1;66H\\\u001b[3;66H\\\u001b[14;66H\\\u001b[16;66H\\\u001b[16;1H"]
[921.194716, "o", "\u001b[16;1H\u001b[17;1H\u001b[7m-----Info: (coreutils)touch invocation, 173 lines --65%-----------\u001b[0m\u001b[1;1Houpled\u001b[K\u001b[2;1H     with option ‘-r’, a reference timestamp is taken from a symb\u001b[2;66H\\\u001b[3;1Holic\u001b[K\u001b[4;1H     link rather than the file it refers to.\u001b[5;1H\u001b[K\u001b[6;1H‘-m’\u001b[7;3H-time=mtime’\u001b[8;10Hodify’\u001b[9;1H     Change the modification timestamp only.\u001b[10;1H\u001b[K\u001b[11;1H‘-r FILE’\u001b[12;3H-reference=FILE’\u001b[13;1H     Use the times of the reference FILE instead of the current t\u001b[13;66H\\\u001b[14;1Hime.\u001b[K\u001b[15;1H     If this option is combined with the ‘--date=TIME’ (‘-d TIME’\u001b[15;66H\\\u001b[16;1H)\u001b[K\u001b[16;1H\u001b[2;66H\\\u001b[13;66H\\\u001b[15;66H\\\u001b[16;1H"]
[921.226292, "o", "\u001b[16;1H\u001b[17;1H\u001b[7m-----Info: (coreutils)touch invocation, 173 lines --66%-----------\u001b[0m\u001b[1;1H     with option ‘-r’, a reference timestamp is taken from a symb\u001b[1;66H\\\u001b[2;1Holic\u001b[K\u001b[3;1H     link rather than the file it refers to.\u001b[4;1H\u001b[K\u001b[5;1H‘-m’\u001b[6;3H-time=mtime’\u001b[7;10Hodify’\u001b[8;1H     Change the modification timestamp only.\u001b[9;1H\u001b[K\u001b[10;1H‘-r FILE’\u001b[11;3H-reference=FILE’\u001b[12;1H     Use the times of the reference FILE instead of the current t\u001b[12;66H\\\u001b[13;1Hime.\u001b[K\u001b[14;1H     If this option is combined with the ‘--date=TIME’ (‘-d TIME’\u001b[14;66H\\\u001b[15;1H)\u001b[K\u001b[16;1H     option, the reference FILE’s time is the origin for any rela\u001b[16;66H\\\u001b[16;1H\u001b[1;66H\\\u001b[12;66H\\\u001b[14;66H\\\u001b[16;66H\\\u001b[16;1H"]
[921.257809, "o", "\u001b[16;1H\u001b[1;1Holic\u001b[K\u001b[2;1H     link rather than the file it refers to.\u001b[3;1H\u001b[K\u001b[4;1H‘-m’\u001b[5;3H-time=mtime’\u001b[6;10Hodify’\u001b[7;1H     Change the modification timestamp only.\u001b[8;1H\u001b[K\u001b[9;1H‘-r FILE’\u001b[10;3H-reference=FILE’\u001b[11;1H     Use the times of the reference FILE instead of the current t\u001b[11;66H\\\u001b[12;1Hime.\u001b[K\u001b[13;1H     If this option is combined with the ‘--date=TIME’ (‘-d TIME’\u001b[13;66H\\\u001b[14;1H)\u001b[K\u001b[15;1H     option, the reference FILE’s time is the origin for any rela\u001b[15;66H\\\u001b[16;1Htive\u001b[K\u001b[16;1H\u001b[11;66H\\\u001b[13;66H\\\u001b[15;66H\\\u001b[16;1H"]
[921.639554, "o", "\u001b[16;1H\u001b[1;16r\u001b[14S\u001b[1;18r\u001b[17;1H\u001b[7m-----Info: (coreutils)touch invocation, 173 lines --75%-----------\u001b[0m\u001b[1;66H\\\u001b[3;1H     TIMEs given, but is otherwise ignored.  For example, ‘-r foo\u001b[3;66H\\\u001b[4;1H -d '-5\u001b[5;1H     seconds'’ specifies a timestamp equal to five seconds before\u001b[5;66H\\\u001b[6;1H the\u001b[7;1H     corresponding timestamp for ‘foo’.  If FILE is a symbolic li\u001b[7;66H\\\u001b[8;1Hnk, the\u001b[9;1H     reference timestamp is taken from the target of the symlink,\u001b[9;66H\\\u001b[10;1H unless\u001b[11;1H     ‘-h’ was also in effect.\u001b[13;1H‘-t [[CC]YY]MMDDHHMM[.SS]’\u001b[14;1H     Use the argument (optional four-digit or two-digit years, mo\u001b[14;66H\\\u001b[15;1Hnths,\u001b[16;1H     days, hours, minutes, optional seconds) instead of the curre\u001b[16;66H\\\u001b[1;66H\\\u001b[3;66H\\\u001b[5;66H\\\u001b[7;66H\\\u001b[9;66H\\\u001b[14;66H\\\u001b[16;66H\\\u001b[2;1H"]
[922.030183, "o", "\u001b[2;1H\u001b[1;16r\u001b[14S\u001b[1;18r\u001b[17;1H\u001b[7m-----Info: (coreutils)touch invocation, 173 lines --84%-----------\u001b[0m\u001b[2;66H\\\u001b[3;1Hnt\u001b[4;1H     time.  If the year is specified with only two digits, then C\u001b[4;66H\\\u001b[5;1HC is 20\u001b[6;1H     for years in the range 0 ... 68, and 19 for years in 69 ... \u001b[6;66H\\\u001b[7;1H99.  If\u001b[8;1H     no digits of the year are specified, the argument is interpr\u001b[8;66H\\\u001b[9;1Heted as\u001b[10;1H     a date in the current year.  On the atypical systems that su\u001b[10;66H\\\u001b[11;1Hpport\u001b[12;1H     leap seconds, SS may be ‘60’.\u001b[14;1H   On systems predating POSIX 1003.1-2001, ‘touch’ supports an ob\u001b[14;66H\\\u001b[15;1Hsolete\u001b[16;1Hsyntax, as follows.  If no timestamp is given with any of the ‘-d\u001b[16;66H\\\u001b[2;66H\\\u001b[4;66H\\\u001b[6;66H\\\u001b[8;66H\\\u001b[10;66H\\\u001b[14;66H\\\u001b[16;66H\\\u001b[1;1H"]
[922.216438, "o", "\u001b[1;1H\u001b[1;16r\u001b[14S\u001b[1;18r\u001b[17;1H\u001b[7m-----Info: (coreutils)touch invocation, 173 lines --93%-----------\u001b[0m\u001b[2;66H\\\u001b[3;1H’,\u001b[4;1H‘-r’, or ‘-t’ options, and if there are two or more FILEs and the\u001b[4;66H\\\u001b[5;1H first\u001b[6;1HFILE is of the form ‘MMDDHHMM[YY]’ and this would be a valid argu\u001b[6;66H\\\u001b[7;1Hment to\u001b[8;1Hthe ‘-t’ option (if the YY, if any, were moved to the front), and\u001b[8;66H\\\u001b[9;1H if the\u001b[10;1Hrepresented year is in the range 1969–1999, that argument is inte\u001b[10;66H\\\u001b[11;1Hrpreted\u001b[12;1Has the time for the other files instead of as a file name.  Altho\u001b[12;66H\\\u001b[13;1Hugh\u001b[14;1Hthis obsolete behavior can be controlled with the ‘_POSIX2_VERSIO\u001b[14;66H\\\u001b[15;1HN’\u001b[16;1Henvironment variable (\u001b[4m*note Standards conformance\u001b[24m::), portable sc\u001b[K\u001b[16;66H\\\u001b[2;66H\\\u001b[4;66H\\\u001b[6;66H\\\u001b[8;66H\\\u001b[10;66H\\\u001b[12;66H\\\u001b[14;66H\\\u001b[16;66H\\\u001b[1;1H"]
[922.411076, "o", "\u001b[1;1H\u001b[1;16r\u001b[14S\u001b[1;18r\u001b[17;1H\u001b[7m-----Info: (coreutils)touch invocation, 173 lines --Bot-----------\u001b[0m\u001b[2;66H\\\u001b[3;1Hripts\u001b[4;1Hshould avoid commands whose behavior depends on this variable.  F\u001b[4;66H\\\u001b[5;1Hor\u001b[6;1Hexample, use ‘touch ./12312359 main.c’ or ‘touch -t 12312359 main\u001b[6;66H\\\u001b[7;1H.c’\u001b[8;1Hrather than the ambiguous ‘touch 12312359 main.c’.\u001b[10;1H   An exit status of zero indicates success, and a nonzero value\u001b[11;1Hindicates failure.\u001b[2;66H\\\u001b[4;66H\\\u001b[6;66H\\\u001b[1;1H"]
[922.591375, "o", "\u001b[1;1H\u001b[17;1H\u001b[7m-----Info: (coreutils)File space usage, 22 lines --Top------------\u001b[0m\u001b[1;2Hext: Printing text,  Prev: Changing file attributes,  Up: Top\u001b[2;1H\u001b[K\u001b[3;1H14 File space usage\u001b[4;1H*******************\u001b[K\u001b[5;1H\u001b[K\u001b[6;1HNo file system can hold an infinite amount of data.  These comman\u001b[6;66H\\\u001b[7;1Hds\u001b[K\u001b[8;2Heport how much storage is in use or available, report other file\u001b[8;66H\\\u001b[9;1H and\u001b[10;1Hfile status information, and write buffers to file systems.\u001b[K\u001b[11;1H\u001b[K\u001b[12;1H* Menu:\u001b[14;1H\u001b[4m* df invocation\u001b[24m::               Report file system space usage.\u001b[K\u001b[15;1H\u001b[4m* du invocation\u001b[24m::               Estimate file space usage.\u001b[K\u001b[16;1H\u001b[4m* stat invocation\u001b[24m::             Report file or file system status\u001b[K\u001b[16;66H\\\u001b[6;66H\\\u001b[8;66H\\\u001b[16;66H\\\u001b[1;1H"]
