[936.573612, "o", "\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r"]
[936.574329, "o", "Usage: chmod [OPTION]... MODE[,MODE]... FILE...\r\n  or:  chmod [OPTION]... OCTAL-MODE FILE...\r\n  or:  chmod [OPTION]... --reference=RFILE FILE...\r\nChange the mode of each FILE to MODE.\r\nWith --reference, change the mode of each FILE to that of RFILE.\r\n\r\n  -c, --changes          like verbose but report only when a change is made\r\n  -f, --silent, --quiet  suppress most error messages\r\n  -v, --verbose          output a diagnostic for every file processed\r\n      --no-preserve-root  do not treat '/' specially (the default)\r\n      --preserve-root    fail to operate recursively on '/'\r\n      --reference=RFILE  use RFILE's mode instead of specifying MODE values.\r\n                         RFILE is always dereferenced if a symbolic link.\r\n  -R, --recursive        change files and directories recursively\r\n      --help        display this help and exit\r\n      --version     output version information and exit\r\n\r\nEach MODE is of the form '[ugoa]*([-+=]([rwxXst]*|[ugo]))+|[-+=][0-7]+'.\r\n\r\nGNU coreutils online help: <https://"]
[936.574416, "o", "www.gnu.org/software/coreutils/>\r\nReport any translation bugs to <https://translationproject.org/team/>\r\nFull documentation <https://www.gnu.org/software/coreutils/chmod>\r\nor available locally via: info '(coreutils) chmod invocation'\r\n"]
