[2782.581578, "o", "\u001b[4mCHMOD\u001b[24m(1)                  User Commands                 \u001b[4mCHMOD\u001b[24m(1)\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[1mNAME\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n       chmod - change file mode bits\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[1mSYNOPSIS\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n       \u001b[1mchmod \u001b[22m[\u001b[4mOPTION\u001b[24m]... \u001b[4mMODE\u001b[24m[\u001b[4m,MODE\u001b[24m]... \u001b[4mFILE\u001b[24m...\u001b[m\r\n       \u001b[1mchmod \u001b[22m[\u001b[4mOPTION\u001b[24m]... \u001b[4mOCTAL-MODE\u001b[24m \u001b[4mFILE\u001b[24m...\u001b[m\r\n       \u001b[1mchmod \u001b[22m[\u001b[4mOPTION\u001b[24m]... \u001b[4m--reference=RFILE\u001b[24m \u001b[4mFILE\u001b[24m...\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[1mDESCRIPTION\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n       This  manual  page  documents  the  GNU version of \u001b[1mchmod\u001b[22m.\u001b[m\r\n       \u001b[1mchmod \u001b[22mchanges the file mode bits of each given  file  ac‐\u001b[m\r\n       cording to \u001b[4mmode\u001b[24m, which can be either a symbolic represen‐\u001b[m\r\n       tation  of changes to make, or an octal number represent‐\u001b[m\r\n       ing the bit pattern for the new mode bits.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page chmod(1) line 1 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[2783.423033, "o", "\r\u001b[K/"]
[2784.142101, "o", "\u001b[KX\bX"]
[2784.577296, "o", "\r\u001b[K\u001b[1;1H\u001b[4mCHMOD\u001b[24m(1)                  User Commands                 \u001b[4mCHMOD\u001b[24m(1)\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[2;1H\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[3;1H\u001b[1mNAME\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[4;1H       chmod - change file mode bits\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[5;1H\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[6;1H\u001b[1mSYNOPSIS\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7;1H       \u001b[1mchmod \u001b[22m[\u001b[4mOPTION\u001b[24m]... \u001b[4mMODE\u001b[24m[\u001b[4m,MODE\u001b[24m]... \u001b[4mFILE\u001b[24m...\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[8;1H       \u001b[1mchmod \u001b[22m[\u001b[4mOPTION\u001b[24m]... \u001b[4mOCTAL-MODE\u001b[24m \u001b[4mFILE\u001b[24m...\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[9;1H       \u001b[1mchmod \u001b[22m[\u001b[4mOPTION\u001b[24m]... \u001b[4m--reference=RFILE\u001b[24m \u001b[4mFILE\u001b[24m...\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[10;1H\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[11;1H\u001b[1mDESCRIPTION\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[12;1H       This  manual  page  documents  the  GNU version of \u001b[1mchmod\u001b[22m.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[13;1H       \u001b[1mchmod \u001b[22mchanges the file mode bits of each given  file  ac‐\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[14;1H       cording to \u001b[4mmode\u001b[24m, which can be either a symbolic represen‐\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[15;1H       tation  of changes to make, or an octal number represent‐\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[16;1H       ing the bit pattern for the new mode bits.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[17;1H\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[18;1H\u001b[1;1H\u001b[4mCHMOD\u001b[24m(1)                  User Commands    "]
[2784.577412, "o", "             \u001b[4mCHMOD\u001b[24m(1)\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[2;1H\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[3;1H\u001b[1mNAME\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[4;1H       chmod - change file mode bits\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[5;1H\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[6;1H\u001b[1mSYNOPSIS\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7;1H       \u001b[1mchmod \u001b[22m[\u001b[4mOPTION\u001b[24m]... \u001b[4mMODE\u001b[24m[\u001b[4m,MODE\u001b[24m]... \u001b[4mFILE\u001b[24m...\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[8;1H       \u001b[1mchmod \u001b[22m[\u001b[4mOPTION\u001b[24m]... \u001b[4mOCTAL-MODE\u001b[24m \u001b[4mFILE\u001b[24m...\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[9;1H       \u001b[1mchmod \u001b[22m[\u001b[4mOPTION\u001b[24m]... \u001b[4m--reference=RFILE\u001b[24m \u001b[4mFILE\u001b[24m...\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[10;1H\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[11;1H\u001b[1mDESCRIPTION\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[12;1H       This  manual  page  documents  the  GNU version of \u001b[1mchmod\u001b[22m.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[13;1H       \u001b[1mchmod \u001b[22mchanges the file mode bits of each given  file  ac‐\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[14;1H       cording to \u001b[4mmode\u001b[24m, which can be either a symbolic represen‐\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[15;1H       tation  of changes to make, or an octal number represent‐\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[16;1H       ing the bit pattern for the new mode bits.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[17;1H\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[18;1H...skipping...\r\n       or  more  letters from the set \u001b[1mrwx\u001b[7mX\u001b[27m\u001b[1mst\u001b[22m, or a single letter\u001b[m\r\n       from t"]
[2784.577442, "o", "he set \u001b[1mugo\u001b[22m.  Multiple symbolic modes can be  given,\u001b[m\r\n       separated by commas.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n       A  combination  of the letters \u001b[1mugoa \u001b[22mcontrols which users'\u001b[m\r\n       access to the file will be changed: the user who owns  it\u001b[m\r\n       (\u001b[1mu\u001b[22m), other users in the file's group (\u001b[1mg\u001b[22m), other users not\u001b[m\r\n       in  the  file's  group (\u001b[1mo\u001b[22m), or all users (\u001b[1ma\u001b[22m).  If none of\u001b[m\r\n       these are given, the effect is as if (\u001b[1ma\u001b[22m) were given,  but\u001b[m\r\n       bits that are set in the umask are not affected.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n       The  operator  \u001b[1m+ \u001b[22mcauses the selected file mode bits to be\u001b[m\r\n       added to the existing file mode  bits  of  each  file;  \u001b[1m-\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n       causes  them to be removed; and \u001b[1m= \u001b[22mcauses them to be added\u001b[m\r\n       and causes unmentioned bits to be removed except  that  a\u001b[m\r\n       directory's  unmentioned  set  user and group ID bits are\u001b[m\r\n       not affected.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7mal page chmod(1) line 20/162 25% (press h for help or q to"]
[2784.577461, "o", " quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[2786.347358, "o", "\r\u001b[K/\r\u001b[K...skipping...\r\n       The letters \u001b[1mrwx\u001b[7mX\u001b[27m\u001b[1mst \u001b[22mselect file mode bits for the affected\u001b[m\r\n       users: read (\u001b[1mr\u001b[22m), write (\u001b[1mw\u001b[22m), execute (or search for direc‐\u001b[m\r\n       tories) (\u001b[1mx\u001b[22m), execute/search only if the file is a  direc‐\u001b[m\r\n       tory or already has execute permission for some user (\u001b[1m\u001b[7mX\u001b[27m\u001b[22m),\u001b[m\r\n       set  user  or group ID on execution (\u001b[1ms\u001b[22m), restricted dele‐\u001b[m\r\n       tion flag or sticky bit (\u001b[1mt\u001b[22m).  Instead of one or  more  of\u001b[m\r\n       these letters, you can specify exactly one of the letters\u001b[m\r\n       \u001b[1mugo\u001b[22m:  the  permissions  granted  to the user who owns the\u001b[m\r\n       file (\u001b[1mu\u001b[22m), the permissions granted to other users who  are\u001b[m\r\n       members  of  the  file's  group  (\u001b[1mg\u001b[22m), and the permissions\u001b[m\r\n       granted to users that are in neither of the two preceding\u001b[m\r\n       categories (\u001b[1mo\u001b[22m).\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n       A numeric mode is from one to four  octal  digits  (0-7),\u001b[m\r\n       deriv"]
[2786.347383, "o", "ed  by  adding  up the bits with values 4, 2, and 1.\u001b[m\r\n       Omitted digits are assumed  to  be  leading  zeros.   The\u001b[m\r\n       first  digit selects the set user ID (4) and set group ID\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7mal page chmod(1) line 38/162 39% (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
